謝寶全　教授 










謝寶全　教授




















指導教授簡介
指導教授學術成就
實驗室簡介
實驗室成員
實驗室成果
大學部專題








    姓名：謝寶全    教授
    專長：食品微生物學、醱酵食品學
    專長：微生物檢驗、機能性食品開發
    學歷：國立台灣大學農業化學研究所   博士
    E-mail：pchsieh@mail.npust.edu.tw
    研究室：FS206 (電話：08-7703202 #7059)
    實驗室：FS206 (電話：08-7703202 #7434)




一、教授簡介





二、教授課程
        發酵學、食品微生物學、微生物學、微生物學實驗、專題討論、機能性食品
        機能性食品理論與應用












一、學術成就
        (一) 期刊論文
            1.     林正昌、林孟姿、鄧德豐、謝寶全 (2007) 味精廢液之有機液肥的開發，中華生質能源學會會誌，26：53-65
            2.     Chao-Chin Chung, Ho-Hsien Chen and Pao-Chuan Hsieh (2007) Application of the Taguchi method to optimize Monascus spp. culture, J.of Food Processing Engineering, 30:241-254
            3.     Chao-Chin Chung, Ho-Hsien Chen and Pao-Chuan Hsieh (2008) Optimization of the Monascus purpureus fermentation process based on multiple performance characteristics, J. of Grey System,11(2):85-96
            4.     Predner Duvivier, Pao-Chuan Hsieh, Po-Yung Lai and Albert L. Charles (2008) Evaluation of drying methods on antioxidant activity, total phenolic and total carotenoid contents of sweet potato (Ipomoea batatas(L.) Lam.) var. Tainong 73, J. International Cooperation, 3(2):73-86
            5.     Predner Duvivier, Pao-Chuan Hsieh, Po-Yung Lai and Albert L. Charles (2008) Total phenolic content and antioxidant activity of seven extracts of sweet potato (Ipomoea batatas Lam.) as affected by the extracting solvent and the genotype,Recherche, Etudes, Developpement-UEH, Haiti(RED),4(1):20-27
            6.     Predner Duvivier, Pao-Chuan Hsieh, Po-Yung Lai and Albert L. Charles (2008) Effect of the drying process on the antioxidant activity, phenolic and carotenoid contents of sweet potato (Ipomoea batatas Lam.) var. Tainong 57, Etudes, Developpement-UEH, Haiti(RED),4(1):43-4
            7.   Lu M-C, Du Y-C, Chuu J-J, Hwang S-L, Hsieh P-C, et al. 2009. Active extracts of wild fruiting bodies of Antrodia camphorata (EEAC) induce leukemia HL 60 cells apoptosis partially through histone hypoacetylation and synergistically promote anticancer effect of trichostatin A. Arch. Toxicol.83:121-9
